Run the deterministic explicit SEIR model

run_deterministic_SEIR_model.Rd

Run the deterministic explicit SEIR model

run_deterministic_SEIR_model(
  population,
  contact_matrix,
  tt_R0,
  R0_set,
  time_period,
  hosp_bed_capacity,
  ICU_bed_capacity,
  mod_gen = explicit_SEIR_deterministic,
  ...
)

Arguments

population

Population vector (for each age group). Default = NULL, which will cause population to be sourced from country
contact_matrix

Contact matrix to use in the simulation.
tt_R0

Time change points for R0
R0_set

The values of R0 to use for the simulation
time_period

Length of simulation. Default = 365
hosp_bed_capacity

General bed capacity. Can be single number of vector if capacity time-varies.
ICU_bed_capacity

ICU bed capacity. Can be single number of vector if capacity time-varies.
mod_gen

An odin model generation function. Default: `explicit_SEIR_deterministic`
...

Other arguments to pass to parameters_explicit_SEEIR

Value

Simulation output

Examples

if (FALSE) {
pop <- get_population("Afghanistan")
m <- get_mixing_matrix("Afghanistan")
run_deterministic_SEIR_model(pop$n, m, c(0, 50), c(3, 3/2), 365, 100000,
1000000)
}
